Appendix: Technical Specifications

A.1 Performance Comparison

Metric 2023 Prototypes 2025 Prototypes Physical Limit Notes
Size (μm) 100-500 70-300 Diffusion (~10) Smaller than red blood cell
Speed (μm/s) 20-50 50-150 Brownian ~10 RMS 1 body length/second
Memory (bits) 64 128-512 Landauer's kT ln2 Enough for 8-64 instructions
Power (pW) 5-10 8-15 Harvesting limit Requires continuous light
Swarm Size 10 ~100 Info theory C=5-20 bps Coordination bottleneck
Sensing Resolution (°C) 1.0 0.3-1.0 Thermal noise Single modality (temp)
Cost ($/robot) 0.05-0.10 0.02-0.05 CMOS scaling $0.003 by 2030 projected

A.2 Current Specifications (December 2025)

```
Size: 70×70×5 μm to 300×300×10 μm
Speed: 50-150 μm/s (optimized dilute H₂O₂)
Power: 8-15 pW (standard illumination)
Memory: 128-512 bits
Processor: 8-bit, 1-10 kHz
Sensing: Temperature (0.3-1.0°C)
Communication: 5-20 bits/second (motion encoding)
Addressable units: Hundreds via optical IDs
Max coordinated swarm: ~100 units
Lifetime: 30-180 days (illuminated conditions)
```

A.3 Visual Elements Recommended for Publication

Figure 1: Electrokinetic Flow Mechanism
Description:Illustration showing induced-charge layer around robot electrodes, with slip velocity vectors demonstrating flow direction in low Reynolds number regime (viscous drag >> inertia). Includes computational fluid dynamics simulation results.

Figure 2: Swarm Scaling Curve
Description:Plot of communication capacity (C in bits/s) versus number of robots (N), showing measured data points from 2025 demonstrations and theoretical limit curve following  \text{S/N} \propto 1/\sqrt{N} . Highlight bottleneck at N ≈ 50.

Figure 3: Cost Trajectory Projection
Description:Log-scale graph comparing historical CMOS transistor costs (1970s: $10 → 2020s: $10⁻⁹) with micro-robot cost projections (2025: $0.03 → 2030: $0.003). Includes solar PV cost reduction trajectory as parallel case.

Figure 4: Manufacturing Yield Breakdown
Description:Stacked bar chart showing contributions to overall yield: CMOS processing (95%), release etch (85%), functional operation (40-50%), and testing (80%). Target improvements indicated for each stage.

